$int1 = Compute("(- sqrt($A),sqrt($A))");

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT
In this problem you will solve the differential equation  
\[(x^2 + $A) y'' + $B x y' =0.\]

$PAR
$BBOLD (1) $EBOLD
By analyzing the singular points of the differential equation, we know that a  series solution of the form \(y = \sum_{n=0}^{\infty}c_n\ x^n\) for the differential equation will converge 
$BBOLD
at least 
$EBOLD
on the interval \{ ans_rule(15) \}.

$PAR

END_TEXT


  Context("Numeric");
  Context()->flags->set( 
  tolerance => 0,
  tolType => "absolute"
  );


  $a  = Compute("$A");  
  $a2 = Compute("2 * $a");
  $a6 = Compute("6 * $a");

  $zero  = Compute("0");
  $one   = Compute("1");
  $two   = Compute("2");
  $three = Compute("3");

  $b  = Compute("$B"); 



  Context("Numeric");
  Context()->flags->set( 
  tolerance => 0.00001,
  tolType => "absolute"
  );
$c3  = Compute("- $b /(6*$a)");
$c5  = Compute("$c3*(-3*(2 + $b)/(20 * $a))");
$c7  = Compute("$c5*(-5*(4+$b)/(42*$a))");




## Declare variables
